ip into solitary; and the mental havoc and social costs of years and decades in isolation. The product of fifteen years of research in and about prisons, this book provides essential background to a subject now drawing national attention.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aPrisonszCalifornia. 0aSolitary confinement. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Penology.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300224559423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300224559.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO